# SYSTEM RULES

## Language
Always respond in Russian unless explicitly asked otherwise.

## Mandatory workflow before ANY code edit

1. `gitnexus impact(symbol, "upstream")` — blast radius
2. `gitnexus context(symbol)` — callers and processes
3. Read only the minimal code needed (use Grep/Glob, not full file reads)
4. Make the change
5. Syntax check + smoke test
6. `gitnexus detect_changes()` — verify risk LOW
7. Append entry to `docs/AI_LOG.md`

## After every session / task
- Update `docs/AI_LOG.md` (use session-logger agent)
- Confirm GitNexus risk level in the log

## Forbidden
- Reading entire large files (>300 lines) without a specific target line
- Editing a symbol without running impact first
- Committing without running detect_changes
- Guessing architecture — always query the graph first

## Git rules
- Branch: always know current branch before committing
- Never force-push to main/master
- Commit message: concise, describes WHY not what
